The paper deals with visual question answering, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of linguistic knowledge sources such as WordNet, indicating a possible connection to natural language processing, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the second likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
